  "number": "1.4.5",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  Consider the sets: A = {red, green, blue}, B = {red, yellow, orange}, and C = {red, orange, yellow, green, blue, purple}   Determine the set A intersect B , and write it in set notation.    Determine the set A union B , and write it in set notation.    Determine the intersection of A complement and C and write it in set notation.          The intersection contains the elements in both sets: A intersect B = {red}    The union contains all the elements in either set: A union B = {red, green, blue, yellow, orange}. Notice we only list red once.    Here we are looking for all the elements that are not in set A and are in set C : A complement intersect C = {orange, yellow, purple}      "
